# KlinikApp: Legendary Minimalistic UI Refactor

This plan outlines the transformation of the KlinikApp frontend into a premium, state-of-the-art interface with a "Clinic Coordinator" philosophy. The focus is on high-density information, fluid interactions, and zero-flicker feedback.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This refactor introduces **TanStack Query** as the primary data fetching and state management layer for the Workspace, replacing traditional `useEffect` hooks to enable **Optimistic UI**.

## Proposed Changes

### 🛠️ Infrastructure
#### [NEW] Dependency Installation
- Install `@tanstack/react-query` and `@tanstack/react-query-devtools`.

#### [NEW] [query-client.ts](file:///C:/Users/Lenovo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/klinikapp/frontend/src/lib/query-client.ts)
- Initialize a global `QueryClient` with standard defaults for a snappy SPA.

#### [MODIFY] [layout.tsx](file:///C:/Users/Lenovo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/klinikapp/frontend/src/app/(app)/layout.tsx)
- Wrap the application in a `QueryProvider`.

---

### 🎨 Design System
#### [MODIFY] [globals.css](file:///C:/Users/Lenovo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/klinikapp/frontend/src/app/globals.css)
- Implement a curated HSL/OKLCH color palette for a "premium" feel.
- Add advanced shadow tokens and glassmorphism utilities (`.glass-morphism`).
- Add micro-animation classes for smooth transitions.

---

### 🧩 Components
#### [NEW] [detail-drawer.tsx](file:///C:/Users/Lenovo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/klinikapp/frontend/src/components/ui/detail-drawer.tsx)
- A reusable, high-performance slide-over panel for task and patient details.

#### [MODIFY] [TaskRow.tsx](file:///C:/Users/Lenovo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/klinikapp/frontend/src/components/workspace/TaskRow.tsx)
- Redesign for 36px height (high density).
- Integrate "Detail Drawer" trigger.
- Add hover-triggered action buttons.

#### [MODIFY] [TaskList.tsx](file:///C:/Users/Lenovo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/klinikapp/frontend/src/components/workspace/TaskList.tsx)
- Refine the "Ghost Input" experience: seamless task creation without losing focus.

---

### 📄 Pages
#### [MODIFY] [tasks/page.tsx](file:///C:/Users/Lenovo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/klinikapp/frontend/src/app/(app)/tasks/page.tsx)
- Migrate from `useState` to `useQuery` for fetching documents and tasks.
- Implement `useMutation` with **Optimistic Updates** for:
    - Task status toggling (instant feedback).
    - Task title editing.
    - New task creation.
- Implement the "Detail Drawer" as the primary interaction point for task metadata.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Run `npm run build` to ensure no TypeScript or build errors.
- Verify React Query provider initialization in the browser.

### Manual Verification
- **Ghost Input Test:** Rapidly add 5 tasks without the input losing focus or the UI flickering.
- **Optimistic Toggle Test:** Click a task checkbox; it should appear "DONE" immediately, even before the server responds.
- **Premium UI Check:** Verify glassmorphism effects on the Sidebar and Detail Drawer.
- **Responsive Check:** Ensure the Detail Drawer behaves correctly on smaller screens.
